quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
6,152,"(vi) and do not even draw near to the property of the orphan in his minority except in the best manner; {1} (vii) and give full measures and weight with justice; We do not burden anyone beyond his capacity; {2} (viii) When you speak, be just, even though it concern a near of kin; (ix) and fulfil the covenant of Allah. {3} That is what He has enjoined upon you so that you may take heed.",footnotes:1:That is
6,153,"(x) This is My way -that which is straight: follow it, then, and do not follow other paths lest they scatter you from His path. {1} This is what He has enjoined upon you, so that you may beware.'",footnotes:1:It is an essential corollary of the natural covenant mentioned above that man should follow the way prescribed by his Lord; any deflection from the orders of God
6,154,"Then We gave to Moses the Book, completing the benediction of Allah upon the one who acts righteously, spelling out everything clearly, a guidance and a mercy; so that they may believe in their meeting with their Lord. {1}",footnotes:1:To believe in 'meeting with the Lord' signifies the conviction that one is answerable to God
6,155,"And likewise We revealed this (Book) - a blessed one. Follow it, then, and become God-fearing; you may be shown mercy."
6,156,"(You may no longer) say now that the Book was revealed only to two groups of people before Us {1} and that we had indeed been unaware of what they read.",footnotes:1:The allusion is to the Jews and the Christians.
6,157,"Nor may you claim that: 'Had the Book been revealed to us, we would have been better guided than they.' Surely clear evidence has come to you from your Lord, which is both a guidance and a mercy. Who, then, is more unjust than he who gave the lie to the signs of Allah and turned away from them? {1} And We shall soon requite those who turn away from Our signs with a severe chastisement for having turned away.",footnotes:1:'Signs of Allah' include the teachings embodied in the Qur'an. They are also manifest in the noble life of the Prophet (peace be on him)
